                            {
                                "start": 0,
                                "stop": 11.229,
                                "byte_start": 106496,
                                "byte_stop": 151427,
                                "text": "Justice Breyer has our opinion this morning in Case 12-1128 Medtronic versus Mirowski Family Ventures."
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 11.229,
                        "stop": 144.12,
                        "byte_start": 151427,
                        "byte_stop": 0,
                        "speaker": null,
                        "text_blocks": [
                            {
                                "start": 11.229,
                                "stop": 20.869,
                                "byte_start": 151427,
                                "byte_stop": 189983,
                                "text": "When a patent owner sues a defendant claiming patent infringement, the patent owner bears the burden of proofing his case."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 20.869,
                                "stop": 26.742,
                                "byte_start": 189983,
                                "byte_stop": 213494,
                                "text": "If he doesn\u0027t prove infringement the alleged infringer wins."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 26.742,
                                "stop": 39.441,
                                "byte_start": 213494,
                                "byte_stop": 264276,
                                "text": "This case requires us to decide who bears the burden of proof in the adverse procedural situation when an alleged infringer brings the declaratory judgment action against the patent owner."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 39.441,
                                "stop": 46.614,
                                "byte_start": 264276,
                                "byte_stop": 293010,
                                "text": "The plaintiff in the declaratory judgment action seeks a declaratory judgment that he did not infringe the patent."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 46.614,
                                "stop": 54.477,
                                "byte_start": 293010,
                                "byte_stop": 324462,
                                "text": "Now, this case is actually quite simple but it just sounds complicated when we start out these little words but just think of A suing B."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 54.477,
                                "stop": 58.316,
                                "byte_start": 324462,
                                "byte_stop": 339822,
                                "text": "A, the patentee sues B saying he\u0027s infringing my patent."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 58.316,
                                "stop": 59.809,
                                "byte_start": 339822,
                                "byte_stop": 345778,
                                "text": "He has to prove it."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 59.809,
                                "stop": 62.897,
                                "byte_start": 345778,
                                "byte_stop": 358107,
                                "text": "Now what happens if instead B sues A?"
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 62.897,
                                "stop": 66.537,
                                "byte_start": 358107,
                                "byte_stop": 372736,
                                "text": "He says I want the judgment that I\u0027m not infringing the patent."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 66.537,
                                "stop": 69.639,
                                "byte_start": 372736,
                                "byte_stop": 385066,
                                "text": "Same question but the adverse procedural situation."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 69.639,
                                "stop": 80.671,
                                "byte_start": 385066,
                                "byte_stop": 429265,
                                "text": "Does that change mean that B bears the burden of proving he didn\u0027t infringe instead of A having to prove that B did infringe?"
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 80.671,
                                "stop": 85.937,
                                "byte_start": 429265,
                                "byte_stop": 450267,
                                "text": "Now right now if you have that, you have the answer and the answer is of course it doesn\u0027t make any difference."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 85.937,
                                "stop": 95.459,
                                "byte_start": 450267,
                                "byte_stop": 488406,
                                "text": "The patentee\u0027s burden stays with the patentee and that follows almost ineluctably from three basic legal propositions."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 95.459,
                                "stop": 103.599,
                                "byte_start": 488406,
                                "byte_stop": 520903,
                                "text": "First, the patentee normally bears the burden of proving infringement because he is normally the one to sue B, right."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 103.599,
                                "stop": 117.6,
                                "byte_start": 520903,
                                "byte_stop": 576909,
                                "text": "Second, the burden of proof is a substantive aspect of a claim and third a declaratory judgment is opposed to a normal suit going the other way concerns only the procedural aspects of a claim."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 117.6,
                                "stop": 130.814,
                                "byte_start": 576909,
                                "byte_stop": 629781,
                                "text": "So the logical conclusion is the burden of proof stays in the same place and that\u0027s what we said and we say that partly for the logical reasons I said and also partly for a certain practical reasons which we go into in the opinion."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 130.814,
                                "stop": 133.134,
                                "byte_start": 629781,
                                "byte_stop": 639080,
                                "text": "So we hold the burden of proof stays the same."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 133.134,
                                "stop": 144.12,
                                "byte_start": 639080,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "The patentee has to prove his case irrespective of the form and will reverse a federal circuit decision to the contrary and it\u0027s unanimous."
                            }
                        ]
                    }
                ]
            }
        ]
    },
